# Write a program that asks the user to input his height in centimeters. Your program should convert and display the height in Feet and inches. (Hint: 1 inch equals 2.54 centimeters and 1 foot equals 12 inches).

cm = float(input("Enter your height in centimeters: "))
inches = cm / 2.54
feet = int(inches // 12)
inches = inches % 12
print("Your height is", feet, "feet and", round(inches, 2), "inches.")

# OUTPUT
'''
Enter your height in centimeters: 165
Your height is 5 feet and 4.96 inches.
'''
